lines.text: i called your name out loud in the court yard
but the answer i longed for never came...
broke-a glittering light of two lovers fate...
destiny called them like a silver poem
they follow the dance till the music died out
last time they met was on an earth bed
both knowing they'd meet again in the light
fear not, dear juliet, your romeo's calling
at the end of this song
but here in our hearts you'll always live on

paragraphs.text: i called your name out loud in the court yard the crystal i held was like an old friend the vines crawled the walls the wind held its breath but the answer i longed for never came...
your name, they had said, was cursed beyound measure the families and odds fought with poisoned tongues and yet through the dark of blind bitter hate, broke-a glittering light of two lovers fate...
walls built between us, miles seperate us, yet in our hearts we share the same dream... feelings so strong, we just must carry on, on to a magical world...
destiny called them like a silver poem they follow the dance till the music died out last time they met was on an earth bed both knowing they'd meet again in the light
